NOTE:PROFESSIONAL PROFILE\n\nEducation: BCom (Hons)\, North-West University\, South Africa; MBA in International Management\, Leiden University\, Netherlands.\n\nProfessional Memberships: Member of the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (SAICA); Member of the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants (CIMA).\n\nCareer History: Began career at PricewaterhouseCoopers\, Johannesburg. Joined Zenitel NV (Euronext-listed)\, focusing on strategic analysis and revenue growth. Moved to Ernst & Young Transaction Advisory Services in London\, advising on cross-border financial due diligence and corporate restructuring. Joined Emerging Capital Partners (ECP) as Director in 2014\, focusing on deal sourcing\, investment appraisal\, and portfolio monitoring. Co-founded Alterra Capital Partners in 2020 alongside former Carlyle Africa colleagues.\n\nAreas of Expertise: Private equity deal origination and execution across Africa; transaction advisory; corporate restructuring; ESG and value creation.\n\nSources:\nhttps://ecpinvestments.com/our-people/renschke-volschenk/\nhttps://informaconnect.com/superreturn-africa/speakers/renschke-volschenk/\nhttps://www.marketscreener.com/insider/RENSCHKE-VOLSCHENK-A2P5HO/
